data.event: This assertion is supported by the old name of an adjacent municipality, "Bagacawa" (now known as Tuburan), which means "fiery cauldron" from the Cebuano baga (ember) and kawa (cauldron).

data.event: This event was witnessed by the arrival in 1888 of the alférez, Antonio Alonso, uncle of José Rizal.
